    <title>Visual Editor: Copy/Pasting a block quote copies CSS formatting, not the blockquote tag</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">### Steps to reproduce the behavior</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Create a block quote around some text.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Copy the text, and paste it into another part of the post, and observe that it looks sort of like a block quote...but look at the HTML and you see it's just got the background color set.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">### Expected behavior</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">The entire block quote is copy/pasted
### Actual behavior</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Only a vague imitation of the block quote is copied.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">##### Tested on alpha-3 Nexus 6P, Android 6.0.1 (shown below on emulator)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
